        public CylinderCommand(java.lang.String jointName,
               java.lang.String bodyNameBefore,
               java.lang.String bodyNameAfter,
               Point origin,
               Point commonAxis,
               Point halfPlane,
               java.lang.String type)
                throws NullParameterException,
                       SelfLoopException,
                       InvalidParameterException
        Instantiates a new cylinder command.
        Parameters:
        jointName - The name of the new Cylinder.
        bodyNameBefore - The name of the first body being joined.
        bodyNameAfter - The name of the second body being joined.
        origin - The origin of the joint.
        commonAxis - The point defining the axis about which the joint revolves and slides.
        halfPlane - The point defining the common half plane of the bodies being joined.
        Throws:
        NullParameterException - Thrown if a parameter is null.
        InvalidParameterException - Thrown if 2 parameters occupy the same point.
        SelfLoopException
